Hi Rosa, 

Heath here now, we have just activated it now that the site is live. It's pending approval. Please see the attached screen shot. I'm not sure how long the approval process takes, but here is the link so that you can keep an eye on it: https://www.mollie.com/dashboard/settings/profiles/pfl_UhtdstAc5K/payment-methods

Hi Joel,



Thanks again! Sorry I keep thinking of things.. I was told that the paying by creditcard option could not be included in the test mode but would appear once we went live, I don't see it yet, could you maybe add this to the options?



Thank again and sorry for all the emails!



Rosa

Hi Rosa,

All good now on this one and we just turned off the maintenance.

Hi Rosa,

Sure, I saw you editing the form. Is it ok for to take over the form?

Hi Heath,



Thanks again! I saw that Joel was working on the website and the maintenance mode is on (again?) So maybe he was working on some last things? Also, I think I might have messed something up in the donation form because if you now select 'anders' the field to put the amount doesn't appear anymore…



Sorry and thanks!



Rosa

Hi Rosa, 

Ok awesome, confirming we have made the below changes and turned the maintenance mode off - woohoo!!
@heath All good now on this one. Let me know if you want to run through with it before turning off the maintenance

Hi Heath,


Thank you! Can you set up the page to live now? There are still a couple of small changes we need to make but I think it is good if we have a 'soft launch' before we really go live on the 14th of feb.

- On the donation page the last option is 'other' can you change this to 'Anders' and would it be possible to put a euro sign € in the line you then get to put an amount so that it is clear that is where you can put the amount you want to donate?

o Giving your address when you donate is not obligatory in the Netherlands, can you change this so that address is not an obligatory field?

o If a donation form is not complete you see the following: There was a problem with your submission. Errors have been highlighted below. In dutch this is: Oeps, er ging iets mis met jouw donatie, er staat hieronder aangegeven wat je nog moet aanpassen.

- Something that skipped my attention was that at the bottom of the fundraiser page where you can add the video's and images there are still some English lines, I can't seem to find where and if I can make these changes myself.

Fundraiser comment/ fundraiser youtube embed - OPMERKINGEN / YOUTUBE VIDEO EMBED CODE

Save comment/youtube video - OPSLAAN

Select image - selecteer afbeelding

Save image - OPSLAAN

- When you use the search option and there is nothing you can find this error is also in English:

- Did you find what you are looking for?

- Dutch: Gevonden wat je zocht?

- If not, please search for a new keyword below. Dutch: Zo niet, vul een nieuwe zoekterm in.

Thanks again!



Met vriendelijke groet,


Rosa Douw

Hi Rosa, 

Hope you had a good weekend. Just a quick email to let know the requested updates have now been made.

Hi Rosa, 

Ok great, thank you. We will work through these and get you an update ASAP. 

Hope you are well and speak soon,

Hi Heath,

Below I made a list of all the small details that need our attention. I did most of the changes that I knew how to do myself already so if there are things in this list that I should be able to do myself please let me know because I’d rather have you show me so I know how to do it next time J
- In the donation form:
o we would like to change the donation amounts, I set it already in the form but in the photo’s it still says the higher amounts, I cannot change these photo’s myself can I? I’ve sent a couple of photo’s with our labcoats as attachments, can you use them?
§ First option €50 photo: ‘181205 Kiss Goodbye to MS labcoats MSA Radiologie’
§ Second option €25 photo: ‘181208 KGTMS labcoats Hersenbank 1’
§ Third option €15 photo: ‘181208 KGTMS labcoats Hersenbank’
§ 4th option ‘anders’ photo: ‘181208 KGTMS labcoats Groningen(3)’
o The countries are still in English, did you find a list in Dutch already?
- I’ve added a screenshot of a fundraising page where there are a couple of things that still need translation or other details, I hope that my with great effort but poor result writing helps to explain what I mean J
- The email I sent earlier about the event is for now not relevant anymore because we decided to do things differently but things often change quickly here so I might still come back to you!


Thanks again!


Met vriendelijke groet,

Rosa Douw
